    • Method Detail

      • asEObject

        EObjectQueryStepBuilder<S> asEObject()
        Converts the elements in the current result set into EObjects.

        This method first checks if the element in question is an instance of EObject. If it is an EObject, it is cast down and forwarded. Otherwise, it is discarded, i.e. all non-EObjects will be filtered out. All null values will also be filtered out.

        Returns:
        The step builder, for method chaining. Never null.
